Get 50 reviews of pros and cons, and ratings of Amazon

baseurl <- "https://www.glassdoor.com/Reviews/Company-Reviews-"
companyNum <- "E40371"
sort <- ".htm"

amazonproscons <- map_df(1:10, function(i) {
  cat(" P", i, sep = "")
  pg <- read_html(GET(paste(baseurl, companyNum, "_P", i, sort, sep = "")))
  pg %>% html_nodes(".col-sm-11.pl-sm-lg.mx-0 .v2__EIReviewDetailsV2__fullWidth") %>%
    html_text() %>% data.frame(rev.pros = ., stringsAsFactors = F)
})
##  P1 P2 P3 P4 P5 P6 P7 P8 P9 P10
amazonproscons[,'index'] <- 1:nrow(amazonproscons)
amazonproscons <- amazonproscons %>% 
  mutate(n=substr(rev.pros,start = 1,stop = 4))

amazonproscons1 <- amazonproscons %>% 
  pivot_wider(names_from=n,values_from=rev.pros) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(Pros)) 

amazonproscons1$Pros <- substring(amazonproscons1$Pros,5)

amazonproscons2 <- amazonproscons %>% 
  pivot_wider(names_from=n,values_from=rev.pros) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(Cons))

amazonproscons2$Cons <- substring(amazonproscons2$Cons,5)

amazon <- as.data.frame(cbind(amazonproscons1$Pros,amazonproscons2$Cons))

colnames(amazon) <- c("pros","cons")
amazon$pros <-  gsub("-","",amazon$pros)
amazon$cons <-  gsub("-","",amazon$cons)

rating <- map_df(1:10, function(i) {
  cat(" P", i, sep = "")
  pg <- read_html(GET(paste(baseurl, companyNum, "_P", i, sort, sep = "")))
  pg %>% html_nodes(".mr-xsm.d-lg-inline-block .value-title ") %>%
    html_attr("title") %>% data.frame(rev.rating = ., stringsAsFactors = F)
})
##  P1 P2 P3 P4 P5 P6 P7 P8 P9 P10
amazon <- cbind.data.frame(amazon,rating)
colnames(amazon)[3] <- "rating"

Pros

clean the data-pros

amazon1 <- amazon
amazon1$pros <- amazon1$pros %>% 
  tm::removeWords(., words = stopwords("en")) %>% 
str_replace_all(., "\n", " ") %>% 
  str_replace_all(., "\\[\\w+\\s*[0-9]*]", "") %>% 
  str_squish(.) %>% 
  gsub("\\.","",.) %>% 
  gsub("\\,","",.) %>% 
  tolower()

frequency-pros

amazonpropr <- tm::MC_tokenizer(amazon1$pros)

amazonprotokenCount = as.data.frame(summary(as.factor(amazonpropr), maxsum = 1000))
    amazonprototal = length(amazonpropr)
    amazonprotokenCount = data.frame(count = amazonprotokenCount[[1]], 
                            word = row.names(amazonprotokenCount),
                            amazonprototal = amazonprototal,
                            row.names = NULL)
amazonprotokenCount <- amazonprotokenCount %>% 
  arrange(desc(count)) %>% 
  mutate(per=count/amazonprototal) %>% 
  top_n(10)
## Selecting by per
amazonprotokenCount$word <- factor(amazonprotokenCount$word,levels = amazonprotokenCount$word[order(desc(amazonprotokenCount$per))])
ggplot(amazonprotokenCount,aes(word,per)) +
  geom_col()

two words-pros

amazonbigrams = amazon1 %>% 
  unnest_tokens(., ngrams, pros, token = "ngrams", n = 2) %>% 
  tidyr::separate(ngrams, c("word1", "word2"), sep = "\\s") %>% 
  count(word1, word2, sort = TRUE)

amazonbigrams$word <- paste(amazonbigrams$word1, "", amazonbigrams$word2)
amazonbigrams <- amazonbigrams %>% 
  select(c(word,n))

rmarkdown::paged_table(amazonbigrams)

It is found that the advantages are more about fast-paced work.

They are so different from Amazon, the top two words are free food, from those top two words, we can feel Google has a really enjoyable working environment and great welfare.

comparison pros between google and amazon

common <- inner_join(x=googlebigrams,y=amazonbigrams,by="word")

common <- common %>% 
  mutate(diff=abs(n.x-n.y)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(diff)) %>% 
  top_n(7) %>% 
  select(n.y,n.x,word)
## Selecting by diff
data <- data.frame(common$n.y,common$n.x,common$word)

pyramid(data,Llab = "Amazon",Rlab = "Google",Clab = "Words-pros",Cgap = 1)

## we find that people working in Google has better work life balance, and people in Amazon would have higher chance of geeting cool projects.

find whether the sentiment score of the review has correlation with rating

get the sentiment score amazon

amazon1$word <- paste(amazon1$pros,"",amazon1$cons)
amazon1$index <- 1:nrow(amazon1)

tokens = amazon1 %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word,word)
token <- tokens %>%
  inner_join(get_sentiments("afinn")) %>% 
  group_by(index) %>% 
  summarise(score=mean(value))
## Joining, by = "word"
result <- token %>% 
  inner_join(amazon1,by="index") %>% 
  select(score,rating)

result <- result %>% 
  mutate(rating= as.double(rating)) 
 
m <- lm(rating~score,data = result)
summary(m)
